   Housing Trust Fund Criteria and Procedures - Final
     __________________________________________________________________


   The Housing Trust Fund Handbook Consists of the Following Chapters

   Click on Chapter Title Below to Download PDF Version

   Introduction - MS Word Version
   Includes the Introduction and Table of Contents.

   Chapter 1 - Housing Trust Fund Statutory Criteria - MS Word Version
   This chapter includes relevant criteria related to funding affordable
   housing appearing in the Revised Code of Washington (RCW) 43.185 and
   43.185A. These criteria provide the foundation for Housing Trust Fund
   guidelines and procedures.

   Chapter 2 Housing Trust Fund Guidelines - MS Word Version
   This chapter contains guidelines for the Housing Trust Fund that
   provide guidance for the award and management of all capital moneys
   contained in the Housing Trust Fund.

   Chapter 3 Housing Trust Fund Application Instructions, Forms and Review
   Procedures - MS Word Version
   Chapter 3 Exhibits - MS Word Version
   Some of the Chapter 3 Forms in Excel
   This chapter provides the application questions and instructions
   necessary to make application to the Housing Trust Fund and procedures
   regarding how applications will be received, reviewed, underwritten and
   how awards will be made.

   Chapter 4 Contract Development and Management Procedures (New
   11-14-2001) - MS Word Version
   Chapter 4 Exhibits - MS Word Version
   This chapter specifies how contracts will be negotiated, executed and
   managed during project development.

   Chapter 5 Compliance and Portfolio Management (New 11-14-2001) - MS
   Word Version
   This chapter specifies how contracts are monitored and how issues
   concerning the HTF portfolio are resolved.

   Glossary - MS Word Version

   Questions and Answers - Winter 2001-02 Housng Trust Fund Application
